@baseUrl = http://localhost:3100/api
@usernameA = userA
@usernameB = userB
@usernameC = userC
@usernameD = userD

### Check current flash sale status.
GET {{baseUrl}}/flash-sale/status

###

### USER A PATH: user attempts to buy and should receive a reservationId.
# @name buySuccess
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameA}}"
}

###


### Check status after reservation -> should return `reserved` while reservation is still active.
# @name getActiveAReservation
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/status?username={{usernameA}}

###

@reservationIdSuccess = {{getActiveAReservation.response.body.$.reservationId}}

### payment success.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/pay
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameA}}",
  "reservationId": "{{reservationIdSuccess}}",
  "forceSuccess": true
}

###

### Check status user A after successful payment -> should return `paid`.
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/status?username={{usernameA}}

###

### Attempt to buy again after already paying -> should return `already_paid`.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameA}}"
}

###

### USER B PATH: second user attempts to buy and gets a reservation.
# @name buyFailUser
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameB}}"
}

###

### Check status user B after reservation -> should return `reserved` while reservation is still active.
# @name getActiveBReservation
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/status?username={{usernameB}}

###

@reservationIdFail = {{getActiveBReservation.response.body.$.reservationId}}

### Simulate payment failure -> reservation should stay active after this.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/pay
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameB}}",
  "reservationId": "{{reservationIdFail}}",
  "forceSuccess": false
}

###

### Check status after failed payment -> should still return `reserved` until reservation expires or payment later succeeds.
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/status?username={{usernameB}}

###

### Retry payment for same reservation, now force success -> shoul return success if reservation still active
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/pay
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameB}}",
  "reservationId": "{{reservationIdFail}}",
  "forceSuccess": true
}

###

### Invalid reservation scenario.
### Same user, wrong reservationId. Should return `invalid_reservation` or no reservation depending on state.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/pay
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameB}}",
  "reservationId": "wrong-reservation-id",
  "forceSuccess": true
}

###

### USER C PATH: Cooldown / expiry scenario setup
# @name buyCooldownUser
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameC}}"
}

###

@reservationIdCooldown = buyCooldownUser.response.body.$.reservationId

### Check status for cooldown scenario user -> should return `reserved` immediately after buy.
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/status?username={{usernameC}}

###

### MANUAL WAIT to make sure reservation is expired

### After reservation expiry, status should become `none`.
GET {{baseUrl}}/orders/status?username={{usernameC}}

###

### Buying again immediately should hit cooldown -> should return `cooldown_active` until cooldown TTL passes.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameC}}"
}

###

### MANUAL WAIT step for cooldown expiry.

### After cooldown expires, user should be able to reserve again.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameC}}"
}

###

### User-throttle scenario.
### Run this request repeatedly within one minute for same username to trigger `too_many_requests`.
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "rate-limit-user"
}


### try with user D
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders/buy
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{usernameD}}"
}